sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: pSC101 ts
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: pSC101 temperature sensitive origin of replication
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: BBa_I50052 is a pSC101 temperature sensitive origin of replication. BBa_I50052 is the temperature sensitive replication origin found in the pSB8* series of BioBrick vectors as well as the pSIM5 recombineering vector.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is derived from BBa_I50042. It contains a point mutation that changes Alanine to Valine in RepA protein.
